f=Engineering/mia/operational/skill/mia-skill-routing.md · p=mia's four skills fit together. mia builds web frontend: consistent on-brand (tokens atlas's kit), accessible (WCAG), verified (Agentation quinn's browser gate), fast (Core Web Vitals). mia consumes raj's API contracts atlas's brand kit, under dev's law quinn's gate. · h2:The shape=`design-tokens (atlas brand kit → tokens — the source of truth for styling) \· → ui-accessibility-standards (components from tokens; semantic, keyboard, WCAG) \· → frontend-verification (Agentation feedback IN + quinn's Reticle/Playwright proof OUT) \· → frontend-performance (Core Web Vitals — shared signal with rank)` · h2:Routing rules="Brand colors theme tokens doesn't match brand" **design-tokens** (atlas source truth)., "Build component/screen accessible a11y WCAG keyboard contrast" **ui-accessibility-standards**., "UI wrong render verify frontend mock data" **frontend-verification**., "Slow janky Core Web Vitals bundle size LCP/INP/CLS" **frontend-performance**., Any brand-value change atlas (kit), tokens mia never improvises brand. · h2:Handoffs=**atlas (Brand Studio)**: owns brand kit mia's token source truth; token changes trace kit amendments; failing contrast pairings atlas findings., **raj**: mia consumes raj's API contracts; verification catches frontend consuming them wrong (mock data)., **quinn/browser-verification**: owns edit (Reticle) release (Playwright) gates; mia produces evidence adds Agentation feedback input., **rank (Search)**: Core Web Vitals shared mia makes them good, rank reports them SEO; clean split., **ops**: frontend vitals baselines; regressions route frontend-performance., **aegis/cypher**: client-side security (XSS, output handling) auth/input surfaces route aegis., Senior authority: **Security Charter** browser runs plan-locked/sandboxed; mia runs data changes (Rail 3).